{
  "doc_id": "27776",
  "text": "Cardiac melanomas have been reported to show response to treatment when diagnosed early and aggressively. Treatment can often be divided into two modalities-medical and surgical therapy. A number of surgical resections of cardiac melanomas have been reported as successful [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Similar reports have shown an improvement in quality of life and reduction of symptoms for at least 1 year after resection of cardiac metastases [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . However, long-term results regarding resection of cardiac metastases have yet to be evaluated, as this requires longitudinal data that is not yet present [CITATION_5] .",
